    <h4>Yum! I can't decide which one sounds tastiest! üç±</h4>

    <ul>
      <li>
        <span><strong>ü•¢ Sashimi</strong></span>
        <p>
          Technically not sushi! While sushi is fish that is served with rice
          and may be adorned with other ingredients, sashimi is simply the raw
          fish, served as is.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span><strong>ü•¢ Nigiri</strong></span>
        <p>
          Nigiri is a style of sushi that is made by molding a ball of vinegared
          rice by hand and topping it with a slice of raw fish. It‚Äôs usually
          served with two pieces and can be eaten with the hands.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span><strong>ü•¢ Maki</strong></span>
        <p>
          There are a variety of maki sushi rolls you can order which range in
          size and style.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <hr />

    <p>Which of the three is your favorite?</p>

